{
  "name": "RPlog_16_ABY_Imperial_Gala_Awards",
  "title": "16 ABY: Imperial Gala Awards Ceremony",
  "summary": "In the grand ballroom of the Imperial Museum on Coruscant, Marshal Krieg Inrokana hosts the awards ceremony for Task Force Inquisitor, introducing the visiting Admiral Rall before presenting decorations to assembled officers. One by one Krieg calls up recipients -- Flight Officer Liza Molokai, Squadron Leader Alex Dante, ISB Sergeant Dreven Mecurio, and the stormtrooper TK-4455 -- pinning medals as guests including Jeni, Lokus Arbin, Shael, and the late-arriving Odion applaud from their tables. The commanding Admiral Jal'Dana then takes the stage to deliver a pointed speech on Imperial strength, deception, and ideals, drawing a standing ovation while the Grand Vizier Korolov and the Sith Warlord Davyd move quietly through the crowd. As the formalities wind down, the gathering dissolves into mingling and verbal sparring: Dante and Odion trade philosophy about ambition and flying, Lokus probes Jal'Dana and Davyd with flattery that earns sharp rebukes, and Dreven broods over his unwanted decorations. The evening closes on a web of veiled threats and courtly intrigue, capped by Jal'Dana's parting aphorism that a man is never more truthful than when he admits he is a liar.",
